currentDoc: Your entire life, you've been told you're deathly allergic to bees. You've always had people protecting you from them, be it your mother or a hired hand. Today, one slips through and lands on your shoulder. You hear a tiny voice say "Your Majesty, what are your orders?"

currentSuggestions.original: "Your Majesty, I am a member of the Royal Guard, and I have been sent to protect you from the evil Queen Bee.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "Your Majesty, I am a member of the Royal Guard, and I have been sent to protect you from the evil Queen Bee.

currentSuggestions.original: "Your Majesty," the little bee said, "What are your orders?"
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "Your Majesty," the little bee said, "What are your orders?"

currentSuggestions.original: "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" it asked again.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: "Your Majesty, what are your orders?" it asked again.
